Description: Copenhagen Suborbitals is a non-profit, amateur based space endeavor building a manned space vehicle into a suborbital trajectory.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Copenhagen Suborbitals is a non-profit, amateur based space endeavor building suborbital space vehicles designed to pave the way for manned space flight on a micro size spacecraft, and on a less budget. It is funded entirely by private sponsors and donors. Copenhagen Suborbitals main objective is to launch a manned space vehicle into a suborbital trajectory, reaching a peak altitude beyond the Kármán line 100 km above the surface of Earth, and subsequently landing the spacecraft safely. To fulfill this mission, it designs and constructs a series of launch vehicles and space-crafts, as well as the necessary infrastructure to launch, operate, and recover the equipment. The entire project of Copenhagen Suborbitals is open source, and within the laws of EU-export control, it intends to share all its technical information. Based in Denmark, S.C., Copenhagen Suborbitals was founded in 2008 by Peter Madsen and Kristian von Bengtson, and is staffed only by volunteer part time specialists.

Description: Evacuated Tube Transport technologies (ET3) is a transportation network for passengers and cargo.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: ET3 stands for Evacuated Tube Transport Technologies.  ET3 is literally "Space Travel on Earth" where car sized passenger (or cargo) capsules travel in 1.5m (5') diameter tubes on frictionless maglev.  Air is permanently removed from the two-way tubes that are built along a travel route. Airlocks at stations allow transfer of capsules without admitting air. Linear electric motors accelerate the capsules, which then coast through the vacuum for the remainder of the trip using no additional power. Most of the energy is regenerated as the capsules slow down. ET3 can provide 50 times more transportation per kWh than electric cars or trains, yet is faster than jets. The company et3.com Inc. is an open consortium of licensees dedicated to global implementation of the patented Evacuated Tube Transport system.   The ET3 mission is to provide a fair and open market where licensees may profitably leverage their assets to optimally implement ETT to maximize transportation value for all.

The company shifted its focus in 2008 to compliance and systems management solutions for Microsoft-centric environments, quickly emerging as a leader in its segment. It amassed over 20 million seats under its management, secured a significant number of Fortune 500 companies as its customers and was chosen by Microsoft as a member of the U.S. ISV Managed Partner Program in the High Potential ISV Group. Blackbird Group was particularly strong in the financial, healthcare and government sectors. The company was entirely bootstrapped, took no venture capital investment, and experienced continual profitable growth from its start-up until its successful acquisition by BeyondTrust, Inc. on December 12, 2012. BeyondTrust is a security solution vendor providing Context-Aware Security Intelligence software, listing many Fortune 100 companies among its customers. It is funded by Insight Venture Partners, a leading global private equity and venture capital firm.
Industry Groups: Financial Services, Information Technology, Lending and Investments, Software
